# Python Style

## General
- Python 3.12+, strict type hints on every function and class attribute
- Line length: 100 characters (Black + Flake8)
- No module-level docstrings at the top of files; no obvious inline comments
- Use `msg = "..."` pattern before `raise`, never inline strings in `raise`

## Imports
- Standard library → third-party → local (`app.*`), one blank line between groups
- No wildcard imports

## Types
- Prefer built-in generics: `list[str]`, `dict[str, int]`, `tuple[int, ...]`
- Use `X | Y` union syntax instead of `Optional[X]` / `Union[X, Y]`
- Use `Protocol` for interfaces/ports, not ABC

## Naming
- `snake_case` for functions, variables, modules
- `PascalCase` for classes
- Private helpers: `_single_underscore` prefix

## No module docstrings
```python
# ❌ BAD — file starts with a docstring
"""User entity."""

from dataclasses import dataclass

# ✅ GOOD — imports first, no file-level docstring
from dataclasses import dataclass
```

## raise pattern
```python
# ❌ BAD
raise ValueError("Full name must not be empty")

# ✅ GOOD
msg = "Full name must not be empty"
raise ValueError(msg)
```
